org.openbel.framework.common.external
Class ExternalType

java.lang.Object
  org.openbel.framework.common.external.ExternalType
All Implemented Interfaces:
Externalizable, Serializable, CachingExternalizable
Direct Known Subclasses:
AnnotationDefinitionTable, AnnotationDefinitionTable.TableAnnotationDefinition, AnnotationValueTable, AnnotationValueTable.TableAnnotationValue, DocumentTable, DocumentTable.DocumentHeader, NamespaceTable, NamespaceTable.TableNamespace, ParameterTable, ParameterTable.TableParameter, ProtoEdgeTable, ProtoEdgeTable.TableProtoEdge, ProtoNetwork, ProtoNodeTable, StatementAnnotationMapTable, StatementAnnotationMapTable.AnnotationPair, StatementTable, StatementTable.TableStatement, TermParameterMapTable, TermTable
public abstract class ExternalType
extends Object
implements CachingExternalizable

This class provides a skeletal implementation of the CachingExternalizable interface to minize the effort needed to externalize a type.

Since:
1.3

writeObject

public static void writeObject(ObjectOutput out,
                               Object o)
                        throws IOException
Writes the potentially null object to output. If o is null, one byte is written to the output to indicate that. Otherwise, the written size is the serialized object size plus an additional byte to indicate non-null.

This method doesn't differ in functionality with ObjectOutput.writeObject(Object), including its support for nulls. It exists as an analogue to the other methods here and as a point for documenting how nulls are handled.

Parameters:
out - Non-null ObjectOutput
o - Object being written
Throws:
IOException - Thrown if an I/O error occurs

_from

protected abstract void _from(ObjectInput in,
                              ReadCache cache)
                       throws IOException,
                              ClassNotFoundException
Reads itself from the input. The supplied cache is an ancillary structure allowing the implementing type to reference a cached copy of an object by its hash value.

The use of the cache is not required. However the use or disuse of the cache should be symmetric according to both _from(ObjectInput, ReadCache) and _to(ObjectOutput, WriteCache). Put differently, the cache use should be identical in both methods.

Parameters:
in - Non-null ObjectInput
cache - Non-null Object ReadCache
Throws:
IOException - XXX WUTM
ClassNotFoundException - XXX WUTM

_to

protected abstract void _to(ObjectOutput out,
                            WriteCache cache)
                     throws IOException
Writes this to the output. The supplied cache is an ancillary structure allowing the implementing type to reference a cached copy of an object by its hash value.

The use of the cache is not required. However the use or disuse of the cache should be symmetric according to both #to(Object, ObjectOutput, WriteCache) and from(ObjectInput, ReadCache). Put differently, the cache use should be identical in both methods.

Parameters:
out - Non-null ObjectOutput
cache - Non-null Object WriteCache
Throws:
IOException - XXX WUTM
